==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sechium
<hw>Se"chi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.: cf. F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧chion</ets>; perhaps formed fr. Gr. <?/ cucumber.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The edible fruit of a West Indian plant
(<spn>Sechium edule</spn>) of the Gourd family. It is soft, pear-shaped,
and about four inches long, and contains a single large seed. The root
of the plant resembles a yam, and is used for food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

